<div id=3D"outline-container-3" class=3D"outline-2">
<h2 id=3D"3">Release of ocaml-eglot 1.2.0</h2>
<div class=3D"outline-text-2" id=3D"text-3">
<p>
Archive: <a href=3D"https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-release-of-ocaml-eglot-=
1-2-0/16515/1">https://discuss.ocaml.org/t/ann-release-of-ocaml-eglot-1-2-0=
/16515/1</a>
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orgc2d561e" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"orgc2d561e">Xavier Van de Woestyne announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-orgc2d561e">
<p>
We (at <a href=3D"https://tarides.com/">Tarides</a>) are <b>particularly pl=
eased</b> to announce the release of <a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/=
ocaml-eglot">OCaml-eglot</a> <code>1.2.0</code>, An overlay on <a href=3D"h=
ttps://www.gnu.org/software/emacs/manual/html_node/eglot/">Eglot</a> (the <=
i>built-in</i> <a href=3D"https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-proto=
col/">LSP</a> client for Emacs) for editing OCaml!
</p>

<blockquote>
<p>
<code>ocaml-eglot</code> is an <b>alternative mode</b> to <a href=3D"https:=
//ocaml.github.io/merlin/"><code>merlin</code></a> which uses <a href=3D"ht=
tps://github.com/ocaml/ocaml-lsp"><code>ocaml-lsp-server</code></a> (instea=
d of <code>ocamlmerlin</code>) as the language server. So yes, if you decid=
e to use~ocaml-eglot~, <code>merlin</code> <b>is no longer needed</b>. (Mer=
lin is still used as a library, in <code>ocaml-lsp-server</code>).
</p>
</blockquote>

<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/releases/tag/1.2.0">R=
elease note</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot">Github repository</a=
></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://melpa.org/#/ocaml-eglot">Package on MELPA</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot?tab=3Dreadme-ov-file#=
features">Features list</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot?tab=3Dreadme-ov-file#=
installation">Installation procedure</a></li>
<li><a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot?tab=3Dreadme-ov-file#=
comparison-of-merlin-and-ocaml-eglot-commands">Comparison table with Merlin=
</a></li>
</ul>

<p>
This version discreetly improves the ergonomics of certain orders, gives mo=
re control over customer-side order support and drastically improves error =
handling! Here's the full changelog and, in the meantime, I'm adding the ch=
angelog for version <code>1.1.0</code>, which hadn't been announced:
</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orgd9f0f1e" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"orgd9f0f1e"><code>1.2.0</code></h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-orgd9f0f1e">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>Fix Type-enclosing's buffer update when using <code>caml-mode</code> (<=
a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/48">#48</a>)</li>
<li>Add <code>ocaml-eglot-search-definition</code>, <code>ocaml-eglot-searc=
h-declaration</code> and alternative functions (<a href=3D"https://github.c=
om/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/45">#45</a>)</li>
<li>Fix some warnings on byte-compilation (<a href=3D"https://github.com/ta=
rides/ocaml-eglot/pull/40">#40</a>)</li>
<li>Fix error on on <code>ocaml-eglot-construct</code> (<a href=3D"https://=
github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/40">#42</a>)</li>
<li><code>ocaml-eglot-alternate-file</code> now visits file in other window=
 when prefix argument is set (<a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-e=
glot/pull/51">#51</a>)</li>
<li>Add error-handling for jsonrpc-request (<a href=3D"https://github.com/t=
arides/ocaml-eglot/pull/52">#52</a>)</li>
<li>Maintain more diagnostics for location failure (<a href=3D"https://gith=
ub.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/52">#52</a>)</li>
<li>Fix hole cycle navigation (<a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-=
eglot/pull/53">#53</a>)</li>
<li>Relay on custom request (if it is available) for managing holes (<a hre=
f=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/53">#53</a>)</li>
<li>Implementation of support for experimental client commands (and impleme=
ntation of <code>ocaml.next-hole</code> in the presence of the <code>ocaml-=
eglot-destruct</code> action) (<a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/ocaml-=
eglot/pull/54">#54</a>)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-org22794f9" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"org22794f9"><code>1.1.0</code></h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-org22794f9">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li>A first support for <code>flycheck</code> (<a href=3D"https://github.co=
m/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/29">#29</a>, <a href=3D"https://github.com/tarid=
es/ocaml-eglot/pull/33">#33</a> and <a href=3D"https://github.com/tarides/o=
caml-eglot/pull/37">#37</a>)</li>
<li>Use a more efficient way to ensure that a vector is empty (<a href=3D"h=
ttps://github.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/27">#27</a>)</li>
<li>Made the mode-line "lighter" more conventional (<a href=3D"https://gith=
ub.com/tarides/ocaml-eglot/pull/26">#26</a>)</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orgaf86198" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"orgaf86198">Spotlight on new features</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-orgaf86198">
<p>
Two easily observable features:
</p>
</div>
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li><a id=3D"orgd947820"></a>Finding an identifier<br />
<div class=3D"outline-text-5" id=3D"text-orgd947820">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li><code>ocaml-eglot-find-identifier-declaration</code></li>
<li><code>ocaml-eglot-find-identifier-definition</code></li>
</ul>

<p>
the two commands behave like their analogues (<code>ocaml-eglot-find-defini=
tion</code> and <code>ocaml-eglot-find-declaration</code>) but allow the us=
er to enter the identifier directly:
</p>


<div id=3D"org7e39348" class=3D"figure">
<p><img src=3D"https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/flex020/uploads/ocaml/original=
/2X/5/5835742f3fadaf6054faf15e02c02c842a757e5a.gif" alt=3D"5835742f3fadaf60=
54faf15e02c02c842a757e5a.gif" width=3D"80%" />
</p>
</div>
</div>
</li>
<li><a id=3D"org1575e7d"></a>Searching for a definition or a declaration<br=
 />
<div class=3D"outline-text-5" id=3D"text-org1575e7d">
<ul class=3D"org-ul">
<li><code>ocaml-eglot-search-declaration</code></li>
<li><code>ocaml-eglot-search-definition</code></li>
</ul>

<p>
Allows you to search by type or polarity to find the definition (implementa=
tion) or declaration (signature) of values!
</p>


<div id=3D"orge3bd058" class=3D"figure">
<p><img src=3D"https://us1.discourse-cdn.com/flex020/uploads/ocaml/original=
/2X/f/f48b3cb62a6eb6b81aa141e471e40e6f7641e0ae.gif" alt=3D"f48b3cb62a6eb6b8=
1aa141e471e40e6f7641e0ae.gif" width=3D"80%" />
</p>
</div>
</div>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div id=3D"outline-container-orgc298147" class=3D"outline-4">
<h4 id=3D"orgc298147">Upgrading</h4>
<div class=3D"outline-text-4" id=3D"text-orgc298147">
<p>
The release is available on MELPA, so you can update it using the usual pro=
cess. As always, your feedback is invaluable!
</p>

<p>
<span class=3D"underline">Happy hacking</span>
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
